Given that this is done inside `quay.io/podman/upstream`, my containers.conf is this one: https://github.com/containers/podman/blob/main/contrib/podmanimage/stable/containers.conf Docker defaults to "default" and then podman rewrites it to "host" in this case because of containers.conf.

My understanding (which might be wrong) is that the check in `SpecGenerator::Validate found pkg/specgen/container_validate.go` which reads this:

```
    if s.NetNS.NSMode != Bridge && len(s.Networks) > 0 {
        // Note that we also get the ip and mac in the networks map
        return errors.New("networks and static ip/mac address can only be used with Bridge mode networking")
    }
```

where `s.Networks` is a `map[string]nettypes.PerNetworkOptions` somehow assumes that as soon as we have defined at least one `s.Networks` entry, we "customize" it. So I tried to fix this by not populating this map if the customization options are actually the same as the default. I may be wrong.

Then what about updating this check here:

```
    if s.NetNS.NSMode != Bridge && len(s.Networks) > 0 {
        // Note that we also get the ip and mac in the networks map
        return errors.New("networks and static ip/mac address can only be used with Bridge mode networking")
    }
```

and try to look into the s.Networks and see if some try to define explicitly an ip or mac address which is not an empty string ? (which I guess was indirectly what my first proposed diff was doing, by not populating it if only default values were provided)

So more something like this (I didn't test if it actually compiles) ?

```
diff --git a/pkg/api/handlers/compat/containers_create.go b/pkg/api/handlers/compat/containers_create.go
index c7579ade9..5a5d03886 100644
--- a/pkg/api/handlers/compat/containers_create.go
+++ b/pkg/api/handlers/compat/containers_create.go
@@ -373,6 +373,10 @@ func cliOpts(cc handlers.CreateContainerConfig, rtc *config.Config) (*entities.C
                }
            }

+           if !nsmode.IsBridge() && (len(netOpts.Aliases) >= 0 || len(netOpts.StaticIPs) > 0 || len(netOpts.StaticMAC) > 0) {
+               return nil, nil, fmt.Errorf("BOOM !! This is not ok !")
+           }
+
            networks[netName] = netOpts
        }

```
